# Git Push After Task (Today Only — 2026-07-01)

**Valid only on July 1, 2026.**

When a task is completed and the project has meaningful changes:

1. Stage and commit with a clear message (only when the user has not forbidden commits).
2. Push to the remote GitHub repository (`git push` or `gh` as appropriate).
3. If there is no remote yet, create the GitHub repo and set `origin`.
4. If authentication is missing, run `gh auth login` or configure SSH/HTTPS credentials, then push.

Do not leave completed work only on the local machine when a push was requested or implied.
